This paper deals with the task of intrinsic image decomposition, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The paper proposes a novel unsupervised learning framework for this task, which involves exploring the independence between reflectance and shading, domain invariant content constraint, and physical constraint. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically unsupervised learning, to solve the problem. Hence, it is also likely to belong to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). 

Finally, the paper involves the use of physical constraints to solve the problem, which could make it relevant to the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics).
